## Failure Path Testing

The v0 manual mode runtime does not have an easy mechanism to induce failures from CLI.
Failure paths are tested programmatically in `tests/test_runtime.py`:

- `test_runtime_with_failing_skill` (line 232)
- `test_runtime_storage_on_failure` (line 257)
- `test_stored_failure_trace_retrieval` (line 278)  
- `test_runtime_timeout_handling` (line 322)

These tests verify:
- Failures are captured in RunTrace with `final=failure`
- Error messages are preserved
- Failed traces are persisted to storage

## Recommendation
A future enhancement could add `--fail` or `--simulate-failure` flag for manual mode
to support CLI-based failure testing.

